Risk Management Plan
Olympia Foods, Inc.

I.	Introduction
A Risk Management Program has been implemented at the Olympia Foods, Inc. (Olympia Foods) facility located at 9501 Nevada Avenue in Franklin Park, Illinois, for the reduction of accidental releases of hazardous materials. This Risk Management Plan (RMP) summarizes the management, administrative, procedural, and technological controls that work together to minimize the risk to site personnel, contractors, visitors, and the community and environment at large of hazardous chemical releases. The RMP is organized to correspond with specific U.S. Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) RMP, Program 3 of 40 CFR 68, definitions and requirements of Subpart G, including: 
¿	Introduction;
¿	Olympia Foods policies to protect health, environment, and safety;
¿	Facility identification and regulated substances covered processes;
¿	Hazard Assessment;
¿	Prevention Program;
¿	Five-Year Accident History;
¿	Emergency Response Plan; 
¿	Emergency Communications;
¿	Spill Reporting / Environmental Release Procedures;
¿	Planned changes to improve safety; and
¿	Management Program

II.	Olympia Foods Policies To Protect Health, Environment, and Safety
Risk management and safety are important concerns at Olympia Foods; this RMP formalizes and documents these activities. Olympia Foods is committed to conducting its operations in a safe and responsible manner and to reducing risks to human health and to the environment. It is Olympia Foods' policy to comply with all applicable federal, state, and local rules and regulations.

